19 WHEREAS, the City of Bentonville, Arkansas, and Visit Bentonville have
20 demonstrated a steadfast commitment to cycling through strategic investments
21 in trails, infrastructure, marketing, and community engagement; and
22
23 WHEREAS, Bentonville has established itself as a premier global
24 destination for mountain biking, proclaimed in the title of Mountain Biking
25 Capital of the World because of its world-class trail systems, diverse
26 terrain, seamless connectivity, unparalleled accessibility, and innovative
27 cycling initiatives; and
28
29 WHEREAS, Bentonville, in collaboration with organizations such as City
30 of Bentonville Parks and Recreation, the Runway Group, LLC, Trailblazers,
31 Friends of Arkansas Singletrack, and local businesses, has developed and
32 maintained over eighty (80) miles of trails and has connected its trail
33 systems to over four hundred (400) miles of purpose-built mountain biking
34 trails in the region, contributing to the economic, social, and environmental
35 vitality of the region; and
